{
  "texts": [
    "Enhancing robustness through rigorous testing and incorporating fail-safe mechanisms is essential for reliable deployment.",
    "Potential pathways to addressing these issues include efficient training strategies, model optimisation techniques such as pruning and quantisation, and robust data collection methods.",
    "These approaches are essential for the practical and effective training and deployment of VLMs in HRC manufacturing applications.",
    "One of the significant challenges in VLM-based task planning is the current focus on static scenes, which limits the applicability of these models in dynamic environments.",
    "Real-time task planning in dynamic scenes remains an unresolved issue."
  ]
}